Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MazeChangeListener
    Interface used to receive maze change events.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Direction
    Represents a cardinal direction (North, South, East, West) and provides some functions to iterate over the directions.
    Maze<MC extends MazeCell>
    This class represents the abstract concept of a maze.
    MazeCell
    MazeCell is an abstract class that represents a single cell in a Maze.
    MazeCell.CellState
    CellState is a class that represents the visitation state of a given cell.
    MazeRunner<MC extends MazeCell>
    Abstarct base class for MazeRunners.
    MazeRunnerLauncher
    This is a laucher program that will do the command line parsing and instantiate runners and mazes and run them.
    RandomMazeRunner<MC extends MazeCell>
    This implements a Random Maze Runner for any kind of mazes.
    RandomMazeRunnerTest
    This JUnit test class invokes the Maze solver(s) on a number of input mazes.
    SquareCellMaze
    SquareCellMaze is a Maze of square cells (cells with 4 sides).
    SquareCellMaze.SquareCellMazeFactory
    SquareCellMazeFactory is a Factory Design Pattern that generates a new SquareCellMaze.
    SquareCellMazeTracer
    SquareCellMazeTracer implements the MazeChangeListener interface and outputs a text base trace of the progress of a mazerunner.
